a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/wp1wHdBPhwk/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1193:"<h3>New plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/chartboot-for-wordpress/"><strong>ChartBoot</strong></a> allows to create, edit, and embed Google Charts in WordPress Posts or Pages.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/fast-flickr-widget/"><strong>Fast Flickr Widget</strong></a> lets you add a widget to show your Flickr photos.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/widget-css-classes/"><strong>Widget CSS Classes</strong></a> adds custom widget classes and IDs plus first, last, even, odd, and numbered classes to your widgets.</p>\n<h3>Updated plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://ericulous.com/2007/05/16/wp-plugin-genki-youtube-comments/"><strong>Genki Youtube Comments</strong></a> allows you to grab YouTube video comments and insert them into your own blog.</p>\n<p><a href="http://jetpack.me/"><strong>Jetpack</strong></a> supercharges your self-hosted WordPress site with the awesome cloud power of WordPress.com.</p>\n<p><a href="http://simple-press.com/"><strong>Simple:Press Forum</strong></a> is a feature-rich forum plugin.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/wp1wHdBPhwk" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 24 Jul 2012 14:00:11 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"James";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:27;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"bbPress: bbPress 2.1.1 Released";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"http://bbpress.org/?p=115632";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"http://bbpress.org/blog/2012/07/bbpress-2-1-1-released/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:737:"<p>Released today is <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/bbpress/">bbPress 2.1.1</a>. It fixes a few annoyances that popped up with the 2.1 release, and is a safe update for anyone running bbPress 2.0-2.1.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed Invision, phpBB, and vBulletin importers</li>\n<li>Fixed private/hidden forum bugs</li>\n<li>Fixed topic split meta values</li>\n<li>Fixed theme compatibility logic error</li>\n<li>Fixed role mask issues for shared user installs</li>\n<li>Fixed missing function cruft</li>\n<li>Fixed missing filter on displayed user fields</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Props for this release go out to:  DJPaul, iamzippy, JarretC, Netweb, and villagora.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/bbpress/">Go get it now!</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 23 Jul 2012 16:56:45 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"John James Jacoby";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:28;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress 3.5 Scope Proposal";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=11737";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/BYglsSZcJ-Q/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:778:"<p>The scope for <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a> 3.5 <a href="http://make.wordpress.org/core/2012/07/18/3-5-proposed-scope/">has been proposed</a>. Of note, the planned release date is December 5, with release candidates landing around November 14, and a feature freeze at the end of September.</p>\n<p>WordPress 3.5 will also be introducing the new default Twenty Twelve theme, full support for Apple&#8217;s new super-high-definition Retina displays, and improved user experience and image handling.</p>\n<p>Of course, WordPress 3.5 is still in the planning stages, so these are all subject to change at any time before the feature freeze in September.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/BYglsSZcJ-Q" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 23 Jul 2012 14:00:04 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"James";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:29;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attri